                <blockquote class="mbr-fonts-style display-4">
                <h5 class="mbr-section-title mbr-fonts-style mb-2"><strong>   KEY TAKEAWAYS</strong></h5>
             
                1. To buy bitcoin, the first step is to download a bitcoin wallet, which is where your bitcoins will be stored for future spending or trading. <br><br>
                2. Traditional payment methods such as a credit card, bank transfer (ACH), or debit cards will allow you to buy bitcoins on exchanges that you can then send to your wallet. <br> <br>
                3. Most U.S.-sanctioned bitcoin platforms will require you to provide photo I.D. and other information to make sure you don't break money laundering laws, or try to cheat on taxes. <br> <br>
                4. Bitcoin is still a new asset class that continues to experience a great deal of price volatility, and its legal and tax status also remains questionable in the U.S. and abroad. <br><br></blockquote>
